Class ImageMetadata

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.marcolotz.MapperComponents.ImageMetadata
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<ImageMetadata>, org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable

    public class ImageMetadata
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable, java.lang.Comparable<ImageMetadata>
    After the mapping process, there is no need to keep the Blob itself in image processed object, just a few of its attributes. This class is used in the Reduce phase has a simple representation of the processed image.
    Author:
    Marco Aurelio Lotz

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(ImageMetadata comparedImage)
        Compares two imageMetadata taking as base the imageNumber. It is going to sort from the lower to the higher. A negative integer is returned if this object is lesser than the comparedImage. Zero if they are equal and a positive integer if this object is greater than the comparedImage.
